<Document>
<name>Tioga Pass Road</name>
<description><![CDATA[<h2>Tioga Pass Road</h2><p><i>California, USA · CA-120 across Yosemite, Crane Flat to Lee Vining</i></p><p><b>High-country Yosemite — granite domes, Tuolumne Meadows, exit at 3,031 m to Mono Lake.</b></p><table style='font-family:sans-serif'><tr><td><b>Approx. length:</b></td><td>72 km (44 mi)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Drive time:</b></td><td>3 hrs</td></tr><tr><td><b>Best season:</b></td><td>Late May–October (typically closed Nov–May)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Watch out for:</b></td><td>Closure dates unpredictable each year; bears active near pullouts; no fuel between Crane Flat and Lee Vining</td></tr><tr><td><b>Track points:</b></td><td>127</td></tr></table><hr><p>Highway 120's stretch from Crane Flat over Tioga Pass takes you out of Yosemite Valley's crowds and into the high country John Muir loved best — domes of glacier-polished granite, meadows wide as fields, and an exit through a 3,031 m notch into the Great Basin desert. The road follows an old Mono Indian trade route, then a sheep-driving track, then an 1880s mining road. It is the highest road crossing of the Sierra Nevada and is closed roughly half the year. When it opens — late May to early July, depending on snowpack — drive it.</p><h3>Scenic points marked on this route:</h3><ul><li><b>Olmsted Point</b> — Unusual back-side view of Half Dome and a foreground of glacier-polished granite slabs. Erratic boulders deposited by Ice Age glaciers strewn across.</li><li><b>Tenaya Lake</b> — 2,484 m alpine lake ringed by polished granite — Ansel Adams shot it many times. Sandy beach on the east end.</li><li><b>Tuolumne Meadows</b> — 2,627 m subalpine meadow, Cathedral Peak rising behind. Wildflowers peak July; deer and bear common at dusk.</li><li><b>Tioga Pass</b> — 3,031 m, highest highway pass in California and the Sierra. Steep eastern descent reveals the Mono Basin.</li><li><b>Mono Lake (visible from Lee Vining)</b> — Ancient saline lake (over 760,000 years old) with surreal tufa towers along the south shore. Visit Mono Lake Tufa SR — short walk.</li></ul><hr><p><i>Track geometry is interpolated between named waypoints — use a routing service to snap to actual road for navigation. Waypoints, scenic POIs, and notes are reliable.</i></p>]]></description>
